                                        <div class="textBox right">
                                            The College of Administrative and Human Sciences seeks to provide a
                                            distinguished educational service that leads to the provision of
                                            competencies to
                                            the labor market and in a manner that contributes to raising the development
                                            capabilities of the country and society, and working for excellence in the
                                            educational process at the local, regional and international levels, and the
                                            display in the educational process of ethical, technical and professional
                                            behaviors and dealing responsibly towards the process Educational,
                                            excellence in
                                            quality, initiative and teamwork between students, professors, and
                                            university
                                            administration.
                                            <br/>
                                            <br/>
                                            The College of Administrative Sciences and Humanities is interested in two
                                            aspects of science, the first of which is administrative sciences, which
                                            includes various programs in administrative sciences, including business
                                            administration, both Arabic and English, accounting, international business
                                            administration, marketing, production management, and other administrative
                                            sciences.
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="flexBox justifyContentBetween deanWordBox2">
                                        <div class="textBox left">
                                            Administrative sciences are considered an essential basis for the activity
                                            of
                                            any institution, private or public business organization, or any government
                                            agency, because the requirements for conducting business in any activity are
                                            the
                                            presence of administrators, accountants, economists...etc. The development
                                            and
                                            growth of any country, organization or work body comes through the
                                            efficiency
                                            and capabilities of its administrative and accounting staff, the extent of
                                            their
                                            dedication to their work, their sincerity, sincerity and honesty.
                                        </div>
                                        <div class="textBox right">
                                            The second aspect is the humanities, under which different disciplines fall
                                            under such as linguistics, legislation, law, Islamic studies and other
                                            sciences
                                            related to human sciences.
                                            <br/>
                                            <br/>
                                            The humanities provide the qualifications needed by business organizations
                                            and
                                            state agencies, such as legislators, legal experts, linguists, and others.
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
